msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:964(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:964(para)
msgid ""
"Ruby on Rails is an open source web framework for developing database backed "
"web applications. It is optimized for sustainable productivity of the "
"programmer since it lets the programmer to write code by favouring "
"convention over configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:971(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:971(para)
msgid ""
"To run Ruby on Rails, you should install <application>Ruby</application>, "
"<application>Ruby Gems</application>, <application>Ruby on "
"Rails</application>, <application>lighttpd</application>, "
"<application>MySQL</application> and <application>PHP5</application>. To "
"install Ruby base packages you can enter the following command in the "
"terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:984(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:984(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install ruby ri rdoc libmysql-ruby"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:986(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:986(para)
msgid "To install Ruby Gems package, run the following set of commands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:989(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:989(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"sudo wget http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/11289/rubygems-0.9.0.tgz\n"
"tar -xvzf rubygems-0.9.0.tgz\n"
"cd rubygems-0.9.0\n"
"sudo ruby setup.rb\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:996(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:996(para)
msgid "To install some basic gems, please run the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:999(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:999(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"sudo gem install actionmailer\n"
"sudo gem install activesupport\n"
"sudo gem install actionpack\n"
"sudo gem install actionwebservice\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1006(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1006(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>Ruby on Rails</application> package run the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1009(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1009(command)
msgid "sudo gem install rails --include-dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1012(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1012(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>lighttpd</application> package run the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1015(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1015(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install lighttpd libfcgi-dev libfcgi-ruby1.8"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1017(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1017(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>lighttpd</application> is an Web Server. You can install "
"both <application>apache2</application> package and "
"<application>lighttpd</application> package on same machine, but you can "
"only run one at a time since both of them use the port number 80."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1022(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1022(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>MySQL</application> package, please refer to the "
"<xref linkend=\"mysql\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1026(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1026(para)
msgid ""
"To install <application>PHP5</application> package, please refer to the "
"<xref linkend=\"php5\"/> section."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1033(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1033(para)
msgid ""
"Modify <filename>/etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf</filename> configuration file "
"to setup your domains."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1036(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1036(para)
msgid ""
"You should also enable couple of <application>lighttpd</application> modules "
"for using <application>Ruby on Rails</application>. You can run the "
"following commands to enable those modules:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1040(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1040(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"sudo /usr/sbin/lighty-enable-mod fastcgi\n"
"sudo /usr/sbin/lighty-enable-mod proxy\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1045(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1045(para)
msgid ""
"Let us now verify the modification we did in the "
"<filename>/etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf</filename> configuration file. Run the "
"following commands to stop and verify the modification:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1050(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1050(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"sudo /etc/init.d/lighttpd stop\n"
"sudo lighttpd -f /etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1054(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1054(para)
msgid ""
"If you see any errors, please make sure to address them. The error message "
"you see in the output is the best source for getting more help."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/web-servers.xml:1057(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/web-servers.xml:1057(para)
msgid ""
"Thats it! Now you have your Server ready for your <application>Ruby on "
"Rails</application> applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:17(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2204(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:17(title)
msgid "Version Control System"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:18(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2205(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:18(para)
msgid ""
"Version control is the art of managing changes to information. It has long "
"been a critical tool for programmers, who typically spend their time making "
"small changes to software and then undoing those changes the next day. But "
"the usefulness of version control software extends far beyond the bounds of "
"the software development world. Anywhere you can find people using computers "
"to manage information that changes often, there is room for version control."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:23(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2210(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:23(title)
msgid "Subversion"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:24(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2211(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:24(para)
msgid ""
"Subversion is an open source version control system. Using Subversion, you "
"can record the history of source files and documents. It manages files and "
"directories over time. A tree of files is placed into a central repository. "
"The repository is much like an ordinary file server, except that it "
"remembers every change ever made to files and directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:29(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2216(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:29(para)
msgid ""
"To access Subversion repository using the HTTP protocol, you must install "
"and configure a web server. Apache2 is proven to work with Subversion. "
"Please refer to the HTTP subsection in the Apache2 section to install and "
"configure Apache2. To access the Subversion repository using the HTTPS "
"protocol, you must install and configure a digital certificate in your "
"Apache 2 web server. Please refer to the HTTPS subsection in the Apache2 "
"section to install and configure the digital certificate."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:38(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2225(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:38(para)
msgid ""
"To install Subversion, run the following command from a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:43(command) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2230(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:43(command)
msgid "sudo apt-get install subversion libapache2-svn"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:49(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2236(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:49(title)
msgid "Server Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:50(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2237(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:50(para)
msgid ""
"This step assumes you have installed above mentioned packages on your "
"system. This section explains how to create a Subversion repository and "
"access the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:53(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2240(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:53(title)
msgid "Create Subversion Repository"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:54(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2241(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:54(para)
msgid ""
"The Subversion repository can be created using the following command from a "
"terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:58(command) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2245(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:58(command)
msgid "svnadmin create /path/to/repos/project"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:63(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:63(title)
msgid "Importing Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:64(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:64(para)
msgid ""
"Once you create the repository you can <emphasis>import</emphasis> files "
"into the repository. To import a directory, enter the following from a "
"terminal prompt: <screen>\n"
"<command>svn import /path/to/import/directory "
"file:///path/to/repos/project</command>\n"
"</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:76(title) ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:81(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2252(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2257(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:76(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:81(title)
msgid "Access Methods"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:77(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2253(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:77(para)
msgid ""
"Subversion repositories can be accessed (checked out) through many different "
"methods --on local disk, or through various network protocols. A repository "
"location, however, is always a URL. The table describes how different URL "
"schemas map to the available access methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:88(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2264(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:88(para)
msgid "Schema"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:89(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2265(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:89(para)
msgid "Access Method"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:94(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2270(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:94(para)
msgid "file://"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:95(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2271(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:95(para)
msgid "direct repository access (on local disk)"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:98(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2274(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:98(para)
msgid "http://"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:99(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2275(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:99(para)
msgid "Access via WebDAV protocol to Subversion-aware Apache2 web server"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:102(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2278(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:102(para)
msgid "https://"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:103(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2279(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:103(para)
msgid "Same as http://, but with SSL encryption"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:106(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2282(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:106(para)
msgid "svn://"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:107(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2283(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:107(para)
msgid "Access via custom protocol to an svnserve server"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:110(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2286(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:110(para)
msgid "svn+ssh://"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:111(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2287(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:111(para)
msgid "Same as svn://, but through an SSH tunnel"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:117(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2293(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:117(para)
msgid ""
"In this section, we will see how to configure Subversion for all these "
"access methods. Here, we cover the basics. For more advanced usage details, "
"refer to the <ulink url=\"http://svnbook.red-bean.com/\">svn book</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:124(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2300(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:124(title)
msgid "Direct repository access (file://)"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:125(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2301(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:125(para)
msgid ""
"This is the simplest of all access methods. It does not require any "
"Subversion server process to be running. This access method is used to "
"access Subversion from the same machine. The syntax of the command, entered "
"at a terminal prompt, is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:132(command) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2308(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:132(command)
msgid "svn co file:///path/to/repos/project"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:135(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2311(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:135(para)
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:138(command) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2314(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:138(command)
msgid "svn co file://localhost/path/to/repos/project"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:142(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2318(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:142(para)
msgid ""
"If you do not specify the hostname, there are three forward slashes (///) -- "
"two for the protocol (file, in this case) plus the leading slash in the "
"path. If you specify the hostname, you must use two forward slashes (//)."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:144(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2320(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:144(para)
msgid ""
"The repository permissions depend on filesystem permissions. If the user has "
"read/write permission, he can checkout from and commit to the repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:147(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2323(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:147(title)
msgid "Access via WebDAV protocol (http://)"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:148(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2324(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:148(para)
msgid ""
"To access the Subversion repository via WebDAV protocol, you must configure "
"your Apache 2 web server. You must add the following snippet in your "
"<filename>/etc/apache2/apache2.conf</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:150(programlisting) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2326(programlisting) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:150(programlisting)
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" &lt;Location /svn&gt;\n"
"  DAV svn\n"
"  SVNPath /path/to/repos\n"
"  AuthType Basic\n"
"  AuthName \"Your repository name\"\n"
"  AuthUserFile /etc/subversion/passwd\n"
"  &lt;LimitExcept GET PROPFIND OPTIONS REPORT&gt;\n"
"  Require valid-user\n"
"  &lt;/LimitExcept&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/Location&gt; "
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:160(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:160(para)
msgid ""
"To import or commit files to your Subversion repository over HTTP, the "
"repository should be owned by the HTTP user. In Ubuntu systems, normally the "
"HTTP user is <command>www-data</command>. To change the ownership of the "
"repository files enter the following command from terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:169(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:169(command)
msgid "sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /path/to/repos"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:172(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:172(para)
msgid ""
"By changing the ownership of repository as <command>www-data</command> you "
"will not be able to import or commit files into the repository by running "
"<command>svn import file:///</command> command as any user other than "
"<command>www-data</command>."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:180(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2336(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:180(para)
msgid ""
"Next, you must create the <filename>/etc/subversion/passwd</filename> file. "
"This file contains user authentication details. To add an entry, i.e. to add "
"a user, you can run the following command from a terminal prompt:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:185(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:185(command)
msgid "sudo htpasswd -c /etc/subversion/passwd user_name"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:188(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2344(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:188(para)
msgid ""
"This command will prompt you to enter the password. Once you enter the "
"password, the user is added. Now, to access the repository you can run the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:189(command) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2345(command) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:189(command)
msgid "svn co http://servername/svn"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:191(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2347(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:191(para)
msgid ""
"The password is transmitted as plain text. If you are worried about password "
"snooping, you are advised to use SSL encryption. For details, please refer "
"next section."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:197(title) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2353(title) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:197(title)
msgid "Access via WebDAV protocol with SSL encryption (https://)"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:198(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2354(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:198(para)
msgid ""
"Accessing Subversion repository via WebDAV protocol with SSL encryption "
"(https://) is similar to http:// except that you must install and configure "
"the digital certificate in your Apache2 web server."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:205(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2361(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:205(para)
msgid ""
"You can install a digital certificate issued by a signing authority like "
"Verisign. Alternatively, you can install your own self-signed certificate."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/server/C/vcs.xml:210(para) ../generic/server/C/network-applications.xml:2366(para) ../generic/serverguide/C/vcs.xml:210(para)
msgid ""
"This step assumes you have installed and configured a digital certificate in "
"your Apache 2 web server. Now, to access the Subversion repository, please "
